net.enilink.composition.asm

Interface BehaviourMethodProcessor

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    CacheBehaviourMethodProcessor, MethodDelegationGenerator, SparqlBehaviourMethodProcessor

    public interface BehaviourMethodProcessor
    Implements or transforms methods of a BehaviourClassNode.
    See Also:
    DependsOn, UseWith

    • Method Detail

      • implementsMethod

        boolean implementsMethod(Class<?> targetClass,
                         Method method)
        Returns true if this processor is able to implement method of targetClass. Implementing the given method does either mean to create an implementation for an abstract method or to override a superclass method.
        Parameters:
        targetClass - The defining class of the respective method.
        method - The method that can be implemented.
        Returns:
        true if this processor is able to create an implementation for method, else false.

      • appliesTo

        boolean appliesTo(BehaviourClassNode classNode,
                  ExtendedMethod method)
        Called by the container directly before process(BehaviourClassNode, ExtendedMethod) is called. Returns true if this processor can be applied to the given method. If implementsMethod(Class, Method) returns true then appliesTo(BehaviourClassNode, ExtendedMethod) must also return true for the same method.
        Parameters:
        classNode - The owner of the respective method.
        method - The method that should be implemented or transformed.
        Returns:
        true if this processor is able to implement or transform the method, else false.

      • initialize

        void initialize(BehaviourClassNode classNode)
         throws Exception
        Called once for each distinct classNode before process(BehaviourClassNode, ExtendedMethod) is executed.
        Parameters:
        classNode - The class node that should be initialized.
        Throws:
        Exception - An exception if initialization has been failed.

      • process

        void process(BehaviourClassNode classNode,
             ExtendedMethod method)
      throws Exception
        Implements or transforms the given method.
        Parameters:
        classNode - The owner of the respective method.
        method - The method to implement or transform.
        Throws:
        Exception - An exception if processing has been failed.
